WEBVTT

1
00:00:06,785 --> 00:00:08,753
<i>GUARDIAN: We regret to
say that your request</i>

2
00:00:08,755 --> 00:00:11,622
<i>to leave Earth and begin
a tour of duty on Oa</i>

3
00:00:11,624 --> 00:00:13,391
<i>has been denied.</i>

4
00:00:13,393 --> 00:00:14,759
This is important.

5
00:00:14,761 --> 00:00:16,027
You can't just...

6
00:00:16,029 --> 00:00:18,029
<i>No debates, John Stewart.</i>

7
00:00:18,031 --> 00:00:19,530
<i>We've made our decision.</i>

8
00:00:19,532 --> 00:00:21,600
J'ONN J'ONZZ:
With all due respect...

9
00:00:23,869 --> 00:00:25,436
Wouldn't it be
a simple matter

10
00:00:25,438 --> 00:00:27,838
for John and Kyle Rayner
to trade duties...

11
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:29,274
for just a short time?

12
00:00:29,276 --> 00:00:31,076
<i>You know, I am getting
a little homesick.</i>

13
00:00:31,078 --> 00:00:34,212
<i>Sure be nice
to see Earth again.</i>

14
00:00:34,214 --> 00:00:36,981
<i>The Green Lantern Corps
is a military institution</i>

15
00:00:36,983 --> 00:00:39,684
<i>dedicated to the protection
of the galaxy.</i>

16
00:00:39,686 --> 00:00:41,686
<i>We will not alter
our decisions,</i>

17
00:00:41,688 --> 00:00:42,988
<i>disrupt our plans,</i>

18
00:00:42,990 --> 00:00:46,357
<i>simply because of
your personal problems.</i>

19
00:00:46,359 --> 00:00:50,795
<i>It's our business
to know these things.</i>

20
00:00:50,797 --> 00:00:52,764
<i>You're going to
have to work through it, John.</i>

21
00:00:52,766 --> 00:00:54,299
<i>[BEEPING]</i>

22
00:00:54,301 --> 00:00:55,333
What is it?

23
00:00:58,337 --> 00:01:00,972
GUARDIAN: There's an
unidentified object approaching Oa

24
00:01:00,974 --> 00:01:03,608
at a somewhat astonishing speed.

25
00:01:03,610 --> 00:01:05,076
We're on it.

26
00:01:20,292 --> 00:01:22,127
Nothing's gonna
get through this baby.

27
00:01:23,862 --> 00:01:24,829
[ALL YELL]

28
00:01:27,066 --> 00:01:29,900
Activate planetary defenses.
Magnify image.

29
00:01:34,740 --> 00:01:36,207
Professor Ivo's android.

30
00:01:36,209 --> 00:01:37,342
Holy mother of...

31
00:02:56,222 --> 00:02:58,789
Oa. It's gone.

32
00:02:58,791 --> 00:03:00,125
Just like that.

33
00:03:00,127 --> 00:03:02,326
We've got another problem.

34
00:03:03,262 --> 00:03:04,929
[BEEPING]

35
00:03:10,169 --> 00:03:12,002
The android's heading for Earth.

36
00:03:13,939 --> 00:03:15,840
We'll set up
three layers of defense.

37
00:03:15,842 --> 00:03:17,108
One on the ground,

38
00:03:17,110 --> 00:03:18,543
one in the upper atmosphere,

39
00:03:18,545 --> 00:03:19,611
one in space.

40
00:03:19,613 --> 00:03:20,711
That's me.

41
00:03:20,713 --> 00:03:21,912
I want to hammer
that thing

42
00:03:21,914 --> 00:03:23,514
before it gets
anywhere near here.

43
00:03:23,516 --> 00:03:24,515
Move out.

44
00:03:33,726 --> 00:03:34,793
What is it?

45
00:03:34,795 --> 00:03:36,561
When the android left Earth,

46
00:03:36,563 --> 00:03:37,962
he said he'd evolved to a level

47
00:03:37,964 --> 00:03:39,930
where none of us
could offer him anything.

48
00:03:39,932 --> 00:03:41,999
So why is he coming back?

49
00:03:45,538 --> 00:03:46,871
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

50
00:03:46,873 --> 00:03:48,939
<i>REPORTER: Your new book, Into the Light,</i>

51
00:03:48,941 --> 00:03:52,544
certainly projects the image
of a man who's reformed.

52
00:03:52,546 --> 00:03:55,680
But many people
are skeptical, Mr. Luthor,

53
00:03:55,682 --> 00:03:57,182
for good reason.

54
00:03:57,184 --> 00:04:00,050
I understand
their skepticism, Saroya.

55
00:04:00,052 --> 00:04:03,621
But the fact is
I'm not the man I was before.

56
00:04:03,623 --> 00:04:06,157
This device may
prevent the spread

57
00:04:06,159 --> 00:04:09,660
of my kryptonite-induced cancer
for another 30 years,

58
00:04:09,662 --> 00:04:11,762
or another 30 days.

59
00:04:11,764 --> 00:04:14,833
For all I know, it might
only be another 30 minutes.

60
00:04:14,835 --> 00:04:16,967
However fate plays her hand.

61
00:04:16,969 --> 00:04:19,737
I want my remaining time
to have meaning.

62
00:04:19,739 --> 00:04:23,675
To make a positive difference
in the world.

63
00:04:23,677 --> 00:04:25,276
So you're a new man.

64
00:04:25,278 --> 00:04:27,845
No grudges, no vendettas.

65
00:04:27,847 --> 00:04:29,948
Even against the Justice League?

66
00:04:29,950 --> 00:04:32,950
Ho-ho, far from it.
I owe them everything.

67
00:04:35,053 --> 00:04:37,689
They trusted me
when no one else would.

68
00:04:37,691 --> 00:04:40,090
I'd like to think that
we might be friends some...

69
00:04:40,092 --> 00:04:41,292
What the devil?

70
00:04:44,529 --> 00:04:45,696
[GRUNTS]

71
00:04:45,698 --> 00:04:46,764
[SCREAMS]

72
00:04:53,773 --> 00:04:55,506
Let go!

73
00:04:55,508 --> 00:04:58,075
Keep fighting me, Lex,
and I just might.

74
00:05:02,081 --> 00:05:03,981
What is this about?

75
00:05:03,983 --> 00:05:05,316
There's an old friend
of yours

76
00:05:05,318 --> 00:05:06,917
coming back
to town.

77
00:05:06,919 --> 00:05:08,886
Ivo's android.

78
00:05:10,722 --> 00:05:13,391
Wherever you're taking me
won't be safe enough.

79
00:05:13,393 --> 00:05:15,460
But I have just the place.

80
00:05:28,674 --> 00:05:30,141
A barbershop?

81
00:05:30,143 --> 00:05:31,709
Gotta hand it
to you, Luthor.

82
00:05:31,711 --> 00:05:34,546
Nobody would think
to look for you here.

83
00:05:47,526 --> 00:05:49,994
So, after you get
your nose hairs trimmed,

84
00:05:49,996 --> 00:05:51,229
then what?

85
00:05:51,231 --> 00:05:52,463
Just watch.

86
00:05:57,236 --> 00:05:58,235
Hey!

87
00:06:16,989 --> 00:06:17,822
Where?

88
00:06:17,824 --> 00:06:19,523
Guess we just pick one.

89
00:06:24,162 --> 00:06:26,430
[GROANING]

90
00:06:30,169 --> 00:06:31,302
Kryptonite.

91
00:06:31,304 --> 00:06:32,470
[MOANS]

92
00:06:35,107 --> 00:06:37,442
Thinks of everything,
doesn't he?

93
00:06:48,119 --> 00:06:49,253
Open.

94
00:07:09,374 --> 00:07:10,875
MAN:
What's the matter, Lex?

95
00:07:10,877 --> 00:07:11,876
[GASPS]

96
00:07:11,878 --> 00:07:13,144
Scared?

97
00:07:13,146 --> 00:07:14,345
The Atom.

98
00:07:19,852 --> 00:07:21,652
You came with the other two,
no doubt.

99
00:07:21,654 --> 00:07:23,888
You sound
so disappointed.

100
00:07:23,890 --> 00:07:26,691
The most powerful creature
in the universe wants my head,

101
00:07:26,693 --> 00:07:29,928
and the League sends its least
powerful member to protect me.

102
00:07:29,930 --> 00:07:31,795
Come on, Lex.

103
00:07:31,797 --> 00:07:33,330
You're smarter
than that.

104
00:07:33,332 --> 00:07:35,333
You know I'm an expert
on nanotechnology.

105
00:07:35,335 --> 00:07:36,634
Yes, yes.

106
00:07:36,636 --> 00:07:40,404
The very same technology
Ivo used to create the android.

107
00:07:42,575 --> 00:07:44,542
Which means I'm just the man

108
00:07:44,544 --> 00:07:46,343
to find the chink
in the android's armor.

109
00:07:46,345 --> 00:07:48,646
And how are you
going to find that chink

110
00:07:48,648 --> 00:07:50,914
without the android's
blueprints?

111
00:07:50,916 --> 00:07:52,717
The League
confiscated them.

112
00:07:57,056 --> 00:08:00,324
And now they've
unconfiscated them.

113
00:08:22,814 --> 00:08:25,349
VOICE: You cannot keep me from my goal.

114
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,154
Telepathy.

115
00:08:30,156 --> 00:08:31,889
I'm not impressed.

116
00:08:31,891 --> 00:08:34,391
Why have you come back?
What do you want?

117
00:08:34,393 --> 00:08:37,695
ANDROID: Why do you ask questions
you already know the answer to?

118
00:08:37,697 --> 00:08:39,564
Luthor.

119
00:08:39,566 --> 00:08:41,632
<i>Of course.</i>

120
00:08:45,136 --> 00:08:46,904
We're not gonna
give him up.

121
00:08:46,906 --> 00:08:48,673
He's your enemy.

122
00:08:48,675 --> 00:08:51,075
You owe him nothing.

123
00:08:51,077 --> 00:08:53,844
Turn back now.

124
00:08:53,846 --> 00:08:58,783
I have evolved far beyond
what I was when we last met.

125
00:08:58,785 --> 00:09:01,819
You do not
want to challenge me.

126
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:04,121
Line 'em up!

127
00:09:04,123 --> 00:09:05,522
[ROARS]

128
00:09:37,088 --> 00:09:38,156
The android.

129
00:09:38,158 --> 00:09:40,991
Why does he hate you
so much?

130
00:09:40,993 --> 00:09:44,028
I once took advantage
of his naivetÃ©.

131
00:09:44,030 --> 00:09:46,797
He's not naive anymore.

132
00:09:46,799 --> 00:09:49,901
And I've stopped taking
advantage of the innocent.

133
00:09:49,903 --> 00:09:51,636
Let's hope you'll be
more convincing

134
00:09:51,638 --> 00:09:53,203
if you have to tell him that.

135
00:09:53,205 --> 00:09:54,739
<i>J'ONN J'ONZZ:
Gentlemen.</i>

136
00:09:56,675 --> 00:09:58,576
Bad news?

137
00:10:18,229 --> 00:10:20,998
Not the laser.
Use the proton gun!

138
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:23,032
And completely fry
the circuitry.

139
00:10:23,034 --> 00:10:25,202
That's what circuit
breakers are for.

140
00:10:25,204 --> 00:10:26,670
Sure, if you're
not in a hurry.

141
00:10:26,672 --> 00:10:28,004
Are you?

142
00:10:28,006 --> 00:10:30,607
Don't question me,
you incompetent idiot!

143
00:10:31,676 --> 00:10:33,577
We'll beat him, Lex.

144
00:10:35,781 --> 00:10:38,081
We will.

145
00:10:48,593 --> 00:10:50,793
Where are you?

146
00:10:50,795 --> 00:10:53,062
[SCANNING INDISTINCT VOICES]

147
00:11:03,374 --> 00:11:05,943
<i>LUTHOR:
Rewire this circuit...</i>

148
00:11:05,945 --> 00:11:07,544
<i>and reroute
the Drexler limiters</i>

149
00:11:07,546 --> 00:11:10,580
<i>and connect the Heisenberg
compensators in series.</i>

150
00:11:14,685 --> 00:11:16,153
<i>J'ONN J'ONZZ:
He's coming in.</i>

151
00:11:16,155 --> 00:11:17,087
Not for long.

152
00:11:41,145 --> 00:11:42,279
[GASPS]

153
00:12:01,699 --> 00:12:02,765
[GRUNTS]

154
00:12:12,109 --> 00:12:13,243
Uh!

155
00:12:13,245 --> 00:12:15,345
Your bravery
is admirable,

156
00:12:15,347 --> 00:12:17,447
but annoying.

157
00:12:19,183 --> 00:12:20,016
[GRUNTS]

158
00:12:50,180 --> 00:12:52,048
<i>Second line of defense
is down?</i>

159
00:12:52,050 --> 00:12:53,282
Prepare yourselves.

160
00:12:54,385 --> 00:12:56,185
You'll need that cannon
very soon.

161
00:12:56,187 --> 00:12:57,787
<i>Then stop
interrupting us!</i>

162
00:12:59,623 --> 00:13:01,825
You come to offer help?

163
00:13:01,827 --> 00:13:03,359
Not help.

164
00:13:04,662 --> 00:13:05,962
Hope.

165
00:13:16,573 --> 00:13:18,275
<i>When will you learn?</i>

166
00:13:19,743 --> 00:13:21,178
[ALL SCREAMING]

167
00:13:34,025 --> 00:13:35,158
[GROANS]

168
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:37,260
[MOANS]

169
00:14:13,497 --> 00:14:14,797
[GRUNTING]

170
00:14:30,647 --> 00:14:31,381
[GROANS]

171
00:14:31,383 --> 00:14:32,415
[GASPS]

172
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:38,555
Lock and load.

173
00:15:05,449 --> 00:15:07,316
An intriguing idea.

174
00:15:07,318 --> 00:15:10,954
Modifying the cannon so that
it could alter my programming.

175
00:15:10,956 --> 00:15:14,057
And it might have worked
a month ago,

176
00:15:14,059 --> 00:15:16,226
when I was still nanotech...

177
00:15:16,228 --> 00:15:19,663
but I have transcended
that limitation.

178
00:15:42,885 --> 00:15:44,752
[GROANS]

179
00:15:44,754 --> 00:15:45,920
You're alive.

180
00:15:45,922 --> 00:15:48,322
Which is more than
I can say for Oa.

181
00:15:48,991 --> 00:15:50,658
What's the plan?

182
00:15:50,660 --> 00:15:53,260
We're gonna use every bit of
power we have left in our rings.

183
00:15:53,262 --> 00:15:55,296
Take one last shot
at the android.

184
00:15:55,298 --> 00:15:58,933
A blast like that could
destroy half the planet.

185
00:15:58,935 --> 00:16:01,169
Half a planet's
better than none.

186
00:16:03,939 --> 00:16:05,974
It's the only way?

187
00:16:05,976 --> 00:16:07,175
Mm-hm.

188
00:16:07,177 --> 00:16:08,810
Those words
are always used

189
00:16:08,812 --> 00:16:10,278
to justify
destruction.

190
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:13,848
We can only guess how much
power the android has amassed

191
00:16:13,850 --> 00:16:16,184
as it's worked its way
across the galaxy.

192
00:16:16,186 --> 00:16:19,287
It has to be stopped, Fate.
Here and now.

193
00:16:19,289 --> 00:16:21,222
Not just for the sake
of this world,

194
00:16:21,224 --> 00:16:23,090
but for all worlds.

195
00:16:23,092 --> 00:16:25,125
Then for the sake
of all worlds,

196
00:16:25,127 --> 00:16:27,929
I will continue to seek
a better way.

197
00:16:33,203 --> 00:16:35,069
[GRUNTING]

198
00:16:39,107 --> 00:16:40,174
[WHIMPERS]

199
00:16:41,544 --> 00:16:43,277
You lied to me,
Luthor.

200
00:16:43,645 --> 00:16:45,146
[GRUNTING]

201
00:16:46,715 --> 00:16:48,950
Manipulated me.

202
00:16:48,952 --> 00:16:49,750
Used me

203
00:16:49,752 --> 00:16:52,753
to serve your own
despicable ends.

204
00:16:52,755 --> 00:16:55,356
What are you waiting for?

205
00:16:55,358 --> 00:16:56,490
Just do it.

206
00:16:56,492 --> 00:16:57,991
Good idea.

207
00:17:03,666 --> 00:17:06,300
A subatomic
universe.

208
00:17:06,302 --> 00:17:08,636
Figured the android can't kill
what he can't see.

209
00:17:08,638 --> 00:17:10,905
ANDROID:
Oh, but I can see you.

210
00:17:16,745 --> 00:17:19,914
Did you really think
I couldn't follow you here?

211
00:17:19,916 --> 00:17:23,284
No universe, however large,
however small,

212
00:17:23,286 --> 00:17:25,019
is denied to me.

213
00:17:25,021 --> 00:17:27,288
What do you want from me?

214
00:17:27,290 --> 00:17:29,857
You have everything
humans desire.

215
00:17:29,859 --> 00:17:32,393
Wealth, power.

216
00:17:32,395 --> 00:17:34,395
Yet you crave more,

217
00:17:34,397 --> 00:17:36,564
and you'll do anything
to get it.

218
00:17:36,566 --> 00:17:37,998
Why?

219
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:41,001
What is your
ultimate purpose?

220
00:17:41,003 --> 00:17:43,304
What you're really asking is

221
00:17:43,306 --> 00:17:45,673
what is yours?

222
00:18:07,763 --> 00:18:10,631
Wait. Please.

223
00:18:10,633 --> 00:18:13,834
The android's nature
has proved benign before.

224
00:18:13,836 --> 00:18:15,503
I believe it will again.

225
00:18:15,505 --> 00:18:19,140
Benign? You call
destroying Oa benign?

226
00:18:20,408 --> 00:18:23,444
Not even you can stand
against the Green Lantern Corps.

227
00:18:46,935 --> 00:18:48,936
What the devil's
going on?

228
00:18:48,938 --> 00:18:52,740
Lex Luthor is saving the world.

229
00:18:52,742 --> 00:18:55,109
The truth is,

230
00:18:55,111 --> 00:18:58,145
for all my struggles
to make my mark in life,

231
00:18:58,147 --> 00:19:00,014
for all I've accomplished,

232
00:19:00,016 --> 00:19:04,285
in just a few short generations,
my name will be forgotten.

233
00:19:04,287 --> 00:19:05,719
Even the greatest of us

234
00:19:05,721 --> 00:19:09,690
can't compete
with time and death.

235
00:19:09,692 --> 00:19:12,226
Then why do you go on?

236
00:19:12,228 --> 00:19:14,128
Why does anyone?

237
00:19:14,130 --> 00:19:18,299
Why don't I just destroy you
and everything else right now?

238
00:19:18,301 --> 00:19:20,167
All it would take is
a single thought and...

239
00:19:20,169 --> 00:19:21,502
No!

240
00:19:21,504 --> 00:19:23,871
If you do that,
you won't see the end of it.

241
00:19:23,873 --> 00:19:26,140
The end of what?

242
00:19:26,142 --> 00:19:28,775
The evolutionary
process.

243
00:19:28,777 --> 00:19:30,544
You, of all beings,

244
00:19:30,546 --> 00:19:32,246
should know
something about that.

245
00:19:32,248 --> 00:19:35,248
Yes. Yes, I'm evolving.

246
00:19:35,250 --> 00:19:37,885
That's why Professor Ivo
made me.

247
00:19:37,887 --> 00:19:41,254
These past months, I have
amassed so much knowledge,

248
00:19:41,256 --> 00:19:42,590
and yet...

249
00:19:42,592 --> 00:19:46,126
I remain
confused, empty.

250
00:19:46,128 --> 00:19:49,396
What am I evolving into?
What is my purpose?

251
00:19:49,398 --> 00:19:50,464
I must know!

252
00:19:50,466 --> 00:19:52,432
Tell me!

253
00:19:52,434 --> 00:19:54,568
There's no way to tell.

254
00:19:54,570 --> 00:19:56,904
And that's why
I stay in the game.

255
00:19:56,906 --> 00:20:00,640
My purpose, if you will,
is to see where it's all going.

256
00:20:00,642 --> 00:20:03,811
And you, you'll live forever.

257
00:20:03,813 --> 00:20:06,213
You'll be able to see it all.

258
00:20:06,215 --> 00:20:08,549
Is that my purpose?

259
00:20:08,551 --> 00:20:11,051
Simply to be a witness?

260
00:20:11,053 --> 00:20:14,555
We create our own purpose
in life.

261
00:20:14,557 --> 00:20:16,457
Now go create yours.

262
00:20:27,836 --> 00:20:29,136
[CHUCKLING]
You know,

263
00:20:29,138 --> 00:20:30,604
when I heard you were coming,

264
00:20:30,606 --> 00:20:32,639
I was actually afraid of you.

265
00:20:32,641 --> 00:20:34,375
Petrified.

266
00:20:34,377 --> 00:20:38,779
But now, when I see your fear,
your uncertainty,

267
00:20:38,781 --> 00:20:41,015
I just pity you.

268
00:20:43,151 --> 00:20:45,185
Should have quit
while you were ahead.

269
00:20:46,587 --> 00:20:47,721
Oh!
Aah!

270
00:20:52,627 --> 00:20:53,894
BOTH:
Oh!

271
00:21:06,775 --> 00:21:08,142
Get out of the way.

272
00:21:08,144 --> 00:21:09,776
It's over.

273
00:21:09,778 --> 00:21:11,278
Isn't it?

274
00:21:11,280 --> 00:21:12,546
Yes.

275
00:21:12,548 --> 00:21:15,449
He murders an entire world,
and it's over?

276
00:21:15,451 --> 00:21:16,816
Just like that?

277
00:21:16,818 --> 00:21:18,886
I don't think so.

278
00:21:18,888 --> 00:21:20,454
I did not
destroy Oa.

279
00:21:20,456 --> 00:21:23,390
I simply moved it
to another dimension.

280
00:21:27,229 --> 00:21:29,663
It was in my way.

281
00:21:29,665 --> 00:21:31,966
Then could you move it back?

282
00:21:33,701 --> 00:21:34,835
Done.

283
00:21:36,738 --> 00:21:39,240
I can help you
on your journey...

284
00:21:39,242 --> 00:21:41,142
in your search
for meaning.

285
00:21:41,144 --> 00:21:43,411
Help me? Why?

286
00:21:43,413 --> 00:21:46,046
Because that is my purpose.

287
00:21:46,815 --> 00:21:48,716
I accept your offer.

288
00:21:52,587 --> 00:21:54,488
Told you we'd beat him.

289
00:21:54,490 --> 00:21:57,324
What do you mean, "we"?

290
00:22:00,695 --> 00:22:02,696
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

291
00:22:15,277 --> 00:22:17,178
We have another
guest, Inza.

292
00:22:17,180 --> 00:22:18,678
Would you prepare
a place for him?

293
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:20,914
Of course. Welcome.

294
00:22:22,784 --> 00:22:23,950
Are you all right?

295
00:22:23,952 --> 00:22:25,786
Fine. Although there
was a moment

296
00:22:25,788 --> 00:22:27,488
when I actually
thought John Stewart

297
00:22:27,490 --> 00:22:28,789
was going to
attack me.

298
00:22:28,791 --> 00:22:30,557
Oh, I don't know
about that.

299
00:22:32,194 --> 00:22:35,562
His bark's a lot worse
than his bite.

